And you're
with...

782
00:52:10,134 --> 00:52:12,444
Julia's ah, just a friend.

783
00:52:12,467 --> 00:52:14,572
Oh. . .Oh,
just a friend.

784
00:52:14,600 --> 00:52:17,266
Have a nice lunch.

785
00:52:17,267 --> 00:52:19,566
Nice to meet you.

786
00:52:19,567 --> 00:52:21,444
Nice to meet you.

787
00:52:23,867 --> 00:52:26,132
I can't say I blame him.

788
00:52:26,133 --> 00:52:28,545
If it was anyone but family,

789
00:52:28,567 --> 00:52:30,740
I'd a gotten the boot
a long time ago.

790
00:52:30,767 --> 00:52:33,233
I'm <i>so</i> sorry.

791
00:52:33,234 --> 00:52:35,566
What are you going to do?

792
00:52:35,567 --> 00:52:37,945
I don't know.

793
00:52:37,967 --> 00:52:42,848
So much of what I did was
for Ellen and our future.

794
00:52:44,034 --> 00:52:46,674
Your future isn't over.

795
00:52:47,867 --> 00:52:50,211
Would Ellen want you to
give up your life for her?

796
00:52:50,234 --> 00:52:52,407
She loved you.

797
00:52:52,434 --> 00:52:54,732
I know what a woman wants
for the man she loves,

798
00:52:54,733 --> 00:52:57,199
she wants you to go on and be
even more successful...

799
00:52:57,200 --> 00:53:00,909
For yourself
and Kyle and Teri.

800
00:53:03,134 --> 00:53:05,910
You're such a giving man.

801
00:53:05,934 --> 00:53:08,799
You think about everybody
but yourself.

802
00:53:08,800 --> 00:53:14,182
But John. . .
I'm thinking about you.

803
00:53:16,067 --> 00:53:19,674
If you ever
need anything...

804
00:53:19,700 --> 00:53:22,271
I'm here for you.

805
00:53:33,967 --> 00:53:37,141
Cindy and I have been praying
about this for a long time.

806
00:53:37,167 --> 00:53:40,899
We set the date for our wedding.

807
00:53:40,900 --> 00:53:43,266
It's a week after graduation.

808
00:53:43,267 --> 00:53:45,333
That' s great.

809
00:53:45,334 --> 00:53:47,905
Congratulations.

810
00:53:52,133 --> 00:53:54,374
I'm happy for you son.

811
00:53:54,400 --> 00:53:57,066
Just wish things could
have been different,

812
00:53:57,067 --> 00:53:59,547
we haven't had
much time to talk.

813
00:53:59,567 --> 00:54:01,569
I wanted to be there for you.

814
00:54:01,600 --> 00:54:03,876
Make sure you were
ready for this.

815
00:54:03,900 --> 00:54:05,743
Don't worry Dad.

816
00:54:05,767 --> 00:54:08,866
Cindy and I have learned more
about marriage

817
00:54:08,867 --> 00:54:11,643
from watching you and Mom than
you could ever put into words.

818
00:54:16,400 --> 00:54:19,006
Let's go for another set.

819
00:55:05,667 --> 00:55:07,408
John!?

820
00:55:10,433 --> 00:55:13,539
Her name is Julia Sinclair.

821
00:55:13,567 --> 00:55:17,709
She's become a. . .
a dear friend.

822
00:55:17,734 --> 00:55:19,680
She's amazing.

823
00:55:19,700 --> 00:55:23,113
She listens endlessly
to my whining.

824
00:55:25,500 --> 00:55:28,777
I'm just <i>so</i> lonely, Alexander.

825
00:55:28,800 --> 00:55:32,666
I try to remember what it felt like
to have Ellen

826
00:55:32,667 --> 00:55:35,648
put her arms around me,
kiss me...

827
00:55:38,000 --> 00:55:40,503
But the memory's fading.

828
00:55:40,534 --> 00:55:44,641
Every morning I see Julia
and I'm alive.

829
00:55:47,834 --> 00:55:50,747
I'm afraid I'm falling
in love with her.

830
00:55:50,767 --> 00:55:53,213
I love Ellen...

831
00:55:55,233 --> 00:55:57,941
But I just...

832
00:55:57,967 --> 00:56:02,967
Sometimes I can't stand the thought
of holding her hand

833
00:56:03,834 --> 00:56:08,408
and just being
<i>so</i> completely alone.

834
00:56:10,467 --> 00:56:14,074
Loneliness can be
a terrible thing.

835
00:56:14,100 --> 00:56:17,104
I know-- I'm an expert.

836
00:56:17,134 --> 00:56:20,672
There was a time I thought I had a
loneliness problem,

837
00:56:20,700 --> 00:56:23,533
same as you're feeling now.

838
00:56:23,534 --> 00:56:26,105
I know the signs.

839
00:56:26,134 --> 00:56:31,134
But, John, you haven't got
a loneliness problem,

840
00:56:31,700 --> 00:56:38,083
I think the issue
for you is trust.

841
00:56:40,734 --> 00:56:43,066
Are you free tomorrow night?

842
00:56:43,067 --> 00:56:46,207
I suppose so. . .Why?

843
00:56:46,233 --> 00:56:49,237
You'll have to
trust me on this.

844
00:56:49,267 --> 00:56:50,905
All right?

845
00:56:50,934 --> 00:56:53,999
I remember that night
in temple terrace.

846
00:56:54,000 --> 00:56:55,479
God was speaking to my heart--
I knew that.

847
00:56:55,567 --> 00:56:57,532
God was speaking to my heart--
I knew that.

848
00:56:57,533 --> 00:57:00,233
And I remember getting
on my knees

849
00:57:00,234 --> 00:57:03,738
on the 18th hole of
the golf course and I said,

850
00:57:03,767 --> 00:57:09,012
"Oh, God. . .l give in.

851
00:57:09,033 --> 00:57:12,733
"I never wanted
to be a preacher.

852
00:57:12,734 --> 00:57:16,045
"I never wanted to be
anything in the church.

853
00:57:16,067 --> 00:57:18,877
"I didn't like the church,

854
00:57:18,900 --> 00:57:22,166
but I'll be what
you want me to be

855
00:57:22,167 --> 00:57:24,799
"and I'll do what
you want me to do."

856
00:57:24,800 --> 00:57:29,800
And that call has never left
and God has said,

857
00:57:30,167 --> 00:57:35,776
"I want you to continue as long
as I give you the strength."

858
00:57:35,800 --> 00:57:38,178
The voice was <i>so</i> distinct

859
00:57:38,200 --> 00:57:41,199
that I couldn't misunderstand that
call.

860
00:57:41,200 --> 00:57:44,181
And every Christian is
called to ministry.

861
00:57:44,200 --> 00:57:46,305
Did you know that?

862
00:57:46,334 --> 00:57:49,399
The word ministry
means servant, service.

863
00:57:49,400 --> 00:57:53,033
With a call to do
something for other people

864
00:57:53,034 --> 00:57:56,433
that are less fortunate
than we are.

865
00:57:56,434 --> 00:58:00,866
Jesus took on himself the form of
a servant, the Bible says.

866
00:58:00,867 --> 00:58:06,510
He said, "I did not come
to be served, but to serve."

867
00:58:06,534 --> 00:58:08,605
In Mark 10.

868
00:58:08,634 --> 00:58:12,699
It's tough to do
the will of God.

869
00:58:12,700 --> 00:58:15,699
We have the highest standard
of living in the world.

870
00:58:15,700 --> 00:58:19,366
The highest standard that
the world has ever known.

871
00:58:19,367 --> 00:58:21,938
And yet as a nation
we're in danger

872
00:58:21,967 --> 00:58:25,899
of leaving God out of our lives.

873
00:58:25,900 --> 00:58:28,710
Oh, please, God, forgive me--

874
00:58:32,467 --> 00:58:36,938
forgive me for trying
to do all this on my own.

875
00:58:41,167 --> 00:58:44,046
I need you Lord...

876
00:58:47,600 --> 00:58:51,138
Now more than ever.

877
00:58:51,167 --> 00:58:54,366
The devil will always have
a ship ready

878
00:58:54,367 --> 00:58:57,405
when a man wants
to sail away from God.

879
00:59:01,067 --> 00:59:02,011
You see God gave his son,
Jesus Christ,

880
00:59:02,100 --> 00:59:04,080
You see God gave his son,
Jesus Christ,

881
00:59:04,100 --> 00:59:06,637
to die on that <i>cross</i> for you.

882
00:59:06,667 --> 00:59:09,443
That's the reason
he was there...

883
00:59:09,467 --> 00:59:11,766
John?...

884
00:59:11,767 --> 00:59:14,043
Are you all right?

885
00:59:15,567 --> 00:59:17,444
Yeah!

886
00:59:17,467 --> 00:59:19,866
I've got to go
home, Alexander.

887
00:59:19,867 --> 00:59:24,043
I have some things
I need to do.

888
00:59:24,067 --> 00:59:25,833
Sure...

889
00:59:25,834 --> 00:59:28,610
<i>Let'</i> S

890
01:00:09,467 --> 01:00:11,879
Sweetheart...

891
01:00:15,567 --> 01:00:18,032
Sweetheart...

892
01:00:18,033 --> 01:00:20,843
I know it's been a while,

893
01:00:20,867 --> 01:00:23,711
but I have
something to tell you.

894
01:00:23,734 --> 01:00:26,943
Something to remind you of,

895
01:00:26,967 --> 01:00:32,713
because, well, I was reminded
of it myself tonight.

896
01:00:32,734 --> 01:00:36,133
Let's see...

897
01:00:36,134 --> 01:00:39,099
Been a long time.

898
01:00:39,100 --> 01:00:44,100
I, John, take you, Ellen,

899
01:00:44,767 --> 01:00:48,566
to be my wife.

900
01:00:48,567 --> 01:00:52,966
To have and to hold.

901
01:00:52,967 --> 01:00:57,066
To honor and to treasure.

902
01:00:57,067 --> 01:01:00,433
To be at your side

903
01:01:00,434 --> 01:01:03,299
through sorrow and joy,

904
01:01:03,300 --> 01:01:06,366
in sickness and in health.

905
01:01:06,367 --> 01:01:11,367
To love and cherish you always.

906
01:01:12,934 --> 01:01:17,633
I promise you this

907
01:01:17,634 --> 01:01:21,366
from my heart...

908
01:01:21,367 --> 01:01:25,315
With my soul...

909
01:01:25,334 --> 01:01:29,783
For as long
as we both shall live.

910
01:01:32,567 --> 01:01:36,447
This is my promise to you.

911
01:01:40,534 --> 01:01:43,981
You know, up until now

912
01:01:44,000 --> 01:01:49,074
I thought of taking care of you as
a chore.

913
01:01:49,100 --> 01:01:53,632
But I want you to know,

914
01:01:53,633 --> 01:01:57,433
taking care of you is

915
01:01:57,434 --> 01:02:01,746
an honor. . .a privilege.

916
01:02:06,234 --> 01:02:14,449
This bed. . .
Is my altar, Lord.

917
01:02:14,467 --> 01:02:19,246
And on it is the woman I love.

918
01:02:22,767 --> 01:02:26,613
I give her into your hands.

919
01:02:56,300 --> 01:02:57,766
Well, hi.

920
01:02:57,767 --> 01:02:58,799
Hi.

921
01:02:58,800 --> 01:03:00,299
Come on in.

922
01:03:00,300 --> 01:03:01,506
Thanks.

923
01:03:01,534 --> 01:03:03,536
I'm sorry to
surprise you like this.

924
01:03:03,567 --> 01:03:05,513
Oh no, it's fine.

925
01:03:30,000 --> 01:03:34,745
I have a feeling we're not going to
be running together anymore.

926
01:03:41,700 --> 01:03:43,680
Isn't it strange?

927
01:03:44,800 --> 01:03:48,199
It was your faithfulness
that drew me to you

928
01:03:48,200 --> 01:03:52,080
and now your faithfulness
is taking you away.

929
01:04:10,667 --> 01:04:14,137
John. . .Hi.

930
01:04:14,167 --> 01:04:16,366
Phil, I'm sorry
to bother you.

931
01:04:16,367 --> 01:04:20,474
I just wanted to stop by
and tell you, I am <i>so</i> sorry.

932
01:04:20,500 --> 01:04:22,899
You are absolutely right.

933
01:04:22,900 --> 01:04:24,599
About what?

934
01:04:24,600 --> 01:04:26,511
About me holding the firm back.

935
01:04:26,534 --> 01:04:28,833
I've giving it a lot of a thought and
I understand now,

936
01:04:28,834 --> 01:04:31,599
you were right about it and the
only solution is for me

937
01:04:31,600 --> 01:04:35,033
to give you my share--
controlling interest.

938
01:04:35,034 --> 01:04:37,133
What are you
talkin' about?

939
01:04:37,134 --> 01:04:39,633
I've given it
a lot of thought

940
01:04:39,634 --> 01:04:42,132
and I just think it's
best for all concerned.

941
01:04:42,133 --> 01:04:44,466
So, I just wanted
you to know that.

942
01:04:44,467 --> 01:04:47,641
So I'm sorry I disturbed
you and...

943
01:04:47,667 --> 01:04:49,366
Michelle.

944
01:04:49,367 --> 01:04:51,066
Michelle. . .Hi.

945
01:04:51,067 --> 01:04:51,977
Hello.

946
01:04:52,000 --> 01:04:54,480
So, anyway,
have a nice day.

947
01:04:57,534 --> 01:05:00,378
Who was that?

948
01:05:00,400 --> 01:05:05,110
I think it was
my former partner.

949
01:05:07,434 --> 01:05:10,099
Well, I'm glad you
all could make it.

950
01:05:10,100 --> 01:05:12,733
There's been a few changes here
at Brighton Associates.

951
01:05:12,734 --> 01:05:15,733
We have good news and
we have more good news.

952
01:05:15,734 --> 01:05:20,566
The good news is we're not going
to have anymore problems

953
01:05:20,567 --> 01:05:24,333
with John bailing on meetings and
scaring away clients.

954
01:05:24,334 --> 01:05:26,575
What did you do,
hide his pager?

955
01:05:26,600 --> 01:05:28,443
Not exactly.

956
01:05:28,467 --> 01:05:30,366
He stepped down
from the company.

957
01:05:30,367 --> 01:05:32,210
What?
what?

958
01:05:32,234 --> 01:05:33,804
You've got to be kidding us.

959
01:05:33,834 --> 01:05:35,933
So what's the
more good news?

960
01:05:35,934 --> 01:05:39,381
The more good news. . .
Is that I'm in charge now.

961
01:05:43,400 --> 01:05:45,573
Ah. . .no offense, Phil,

962
01:05:45,600 --> 01:05:49,299
but without John,
I'm not sure we can make it.

963
01:05:49,300 --> 01:05:52,899
Without John?
give me a break.

964
01:05:52,900 --> 01:05:55,799
He hasn't been here
for the last <i>3</i> months.

965
01:05:55,800 --> 01:05:58,399
Come on guys.
we'll be fine!

966
01:05:58,400 --> 01:06:00,299
Where's the old
company spirit here?

967
01:06:00,300 --> 01:06:02,166
Who's going to handle
the European clients?

968
01:06:02,167 --> 01:06:04,932
It took John <i>3</i> years to get them
to sign those contracts.

969
01:06:04,933 --> 01:06:06,810
And they won't even
talk to you, pal.

970
01:06:06,833 --> 01:06:08,813
I'll send them flowers.

971
01:06:10,567 --> 01:06:13,047
Is anybody
hot in here?

972
01:06:13,067 --> 01:06:15,479
Look, I'm with you, Phil,

973
01:06:15,500 --> 01:06:18,606
but I'm not sure we're going to be
able to convince the others.

974
01:06:19,400 --> 01:06:21,380
We'll convince them.

975
01:06:22,000 --> 01:06:23,843
We have to.

976
01:06:31,167 --> 01:06:33,166
I see the laundry truck
has arrived.

977
01:06:33,167 --> 01:06:34,771
Hi, uncle Phil.
how's it going?

978
01:06:34,800 --> 01:06:36,133
Okay. ls your dad here?

979
01:06:36,134 --> 01:06:38,832
No. Why, what's wrong?

980
01:06:38,833 --> 01:06:40,799
Nothin' .

981
01:06:40,800 --> 01:06:43,332
Actually, plenty.

982
01:06:43,333 --> 01:06:44,971
Why?

983
01:06:45,000 --> 01:06:46,980
Your dad turned over the controlling
interest

984
01:06:47,000 --> 01:06:48,999
in the company to me.

985
01:06:49,000 --> 01:06:51,033
Really?

986
01:06:51,034 --> 01:06:53,499
Yeah, really.

987
01:06:53,500 --> 01:06:56,037
It's been a disaster.

988
01:06:56,067 --> 01:06:57,966
I thought that's what
you always wanted.

989
01:06:57,967 --> 01:07:00,299
Yeah, he just dumped everything on
me and split.

990
01:07:00,300 --> 01:07:03,599
The whole office staff is nervous,
some of them have quit.

991
01:07:03,600 --> 01:07:05,599
I'm afraid
if I tell the clients,

992
01:07:05,600 --> 01:07:08,099
I'm going to lose a lot more
than just employees.

993
01:07:08,100 --> 01:07:10,410
He knows how valuable he is
to this company,

994
01:07:10,434 --> 01:07:12,414
he can't just do this.

995
01:07:12,434 --> 01:07:14,744
Look, Dad's been under
a lot of pressure lately

996
01:07:14,767 --> 01:07:16,110
with Mom and everything.

997
01:07:16,134 --> 01:07:18,233
There's a lot of professional people
and places

998
01:07:18,234 --> 01:07:20,407
that can do a much better job
of taking care of your mom

999
01:07:20,433 --> 01:07:22,242
than your dad has.

1000
01:07:22,267 --> 01:07:24,666
You haven't even
seen him with her.

1001
01:07:24,667 --> 01:07:28,444
Are they going to put 1 1/2
teaspoons of honey in her tea,

1002
01:07:28,467 --> 01:07:30,310
just the way she likes it?

1003
01:07:30,334 --> 01:07:32,814
Are they going to read to her out
of the Bible

1004
01:07:32,834 --> 01:07:35,508
and brush her hair every night?

1005
01:07:35,534 --> 01:07:37,999
Do they even know what her
favorite color is?

1006
01:07:38,000 --> 01:07:40,241
Look, uncle Phil,
I love you a lot.

1007
01:07:40,267 --> 01:07:42,440
I always have and I always will

1008
01:07:42,467 --> 01:07:45,433
and I appreciate the things you've
tried to tell me

1009
01:07:45,434 --> 01:07:48,566
about life but, you got
to understand something--

1010
01:07:48,567 --> 01:07:50,599
my father,
he lives every day

1011
01:07:50,600 --> 01:07:53,166
according to the principles
of the Bible.

1012
01:07:53,167 --> 01:07:57,240
Now, I know that doesn't
mean anything to you,

1013
01:07:57,267 --> 01:08:00,544
but I gotta ask you...

1014
01:08:00,567 --> 01:08:04,105
What principles
do you live by?

1015
01:08:16,767 --> 01:08:19,099
If you want to find Dad,

1016
01:08:19,100 --> 01:08:22,604
he's probably at Alexander's.

1017
01:08:41,700 --> 01:08:45,766
And <i>so</i> I did what
you said, Alexander,

1018
01:08:45,767 --> 01:08:48,805
I let go of everything
I could think of...

1019
01:08:50,033 --> 01:08:53,242
And I let go of Ellen.

1020
01:08:55,234 --> 01:08:58,408
I gave her over to God.

1021
01:09:00,534 --> 01:09:05,534
I feel. . .peace.

1022
01:09:06,134 --> 01:09:08,580
Thanks, Alexander.

1023
01:09:22,800 --> 01:09:25,303
Hi, Alexander.

1024
01:09:25,334 --> 01:09:30,334
Phil. . .l didn't know
you were here.

1025
01:09:30,400 --> 01:09:33,199
Well, I heard John
spilling his guts,

1026
01:09:33,200 --> 01:09:35,533
I didn't think
I should interrupt.

1027
01:09:35,534 --> 01:09:38,466
Man, what is
going on with him?

1028
01:09:38,467 --> 01:09:41,209
He let go of the business,
he let go of Julia,

1029
01:09:41,233 --> 01:09:43,372
he let go of Ellen.

1030
01:09:43,400 --> 01:09:45,999
He doesn't have
anything left.

1031
01:09:46,000 --> 01:09:49,166
I mean, how do you get peace
by letting go of everything?

1032
01:09:49,167 --> 01:09:51,866
I thought you get peace
by having everything.

1033
01:09:51,867 --> 01:09:54,366
Well, it's easy enough
to understand,

1034
01:09:54,367 --> 01:09:57,233
but not <i>so</i> easy
when you try and do it.

1035
01:09:57,234 --> 01:10:01,533
You know, I think what matters is
to recognize that it takes

1036
01:10:01,534 --> 01:10:06,199
someone bigger than ourselves
to help us find true peace.

1037
01:10:06,200 --> 01:10:10,866
We weren't designed
to do it alone.

1038
01:10:10,867 --> 01:10:13,733
So how does
John do it?

1039
01:10:13,734 --> 01:10:17,633
He finally recognized
that God was fully capable

1040
01:10:17,634 --> 01:10:20,266
of handling anything
we give him to handle

1041
01:10:20,267 --> 01:10:24,233
and that there is no true peace
without that step.

1042
01:10:24,234 --> 01:10:28,533
I thought God helps those
who help themselves.

1043
01:10:28,534 --> 01:10:34,644
How can he if you're too busy
handling things yourself?

1044
01:10:34,667 --> 01:10:38,911
You see, God loves us <i>so</i> much,

1045
01:10:38,934 --> 01:10:42,973
he gave his only son,
Jesus Christ,

1046
01:10:43,000 --> 01:10:46,470
to die in our place.

1047
01:10:46,501 --> 01:10:51,109
Then he raised him
from the dead

1048
01:10:51,134 --> 01:10:54,240
to prove that he was his son

1049
01:10:54,267 --> 01:10:58,666
and to show us that
we too could have eternal life.

1050
01:10:58,667 --> 01:11:02,766
If he's willing to do all that without
any help from us,

1051
01:11:02,767 --> 01:11:07,011
why should he want to see us
carry our other burdens?

1052
01:11:09,067 --> 01:11:11,206
I don't know.

1053
01:11:11,234 --> 01:11:15,533
Well, he doesn't want us
to carry them.

1054
01:11:15,534 --> 01:11:18,933
And the good news is,
we don't have to.

1055
01:11:18,934 --> 01:11:22,814
He's more than capable
of managing our lives

1056
01:11:22,834 --> 01:11:25,508
if we just let him.

1057
01:11:25,534 --> 01:11:29,346
But we need to acknowledge
that we need him

1058
01:11:29,367 --> 01:11:34,510
and then learn to trust him,

1059
01:11:34,534 --> 01:11:39,534
to believe in him--
let him take control.

1060
01:11:39,601 --> 01:11:44,573
Invite him to be
the Lord of your life.

1061
01:11:46,534 --> 01:11:49,174
So, is that
what John did?

1062
01:11:49,201 --> 01:11:51,181
Uh-hm.

1063
01:11:53,134 --> 01:11:56,308
Is that how he got that
peace he was talking about?

1064
01:11:56,334 --> 01:11:58,133
That' s how.

1065
01:11:58,134 --> 01:12:00,876
You want some of that?

1066
01:12:03,667 --> 01:12:06,375
Sounds like too good
of a deal.

1067
01:12:06,400 --> 01:12:09,381
It's always about the deal.

1068
01:12:11,267 --> 01:12:13,866
But you know-- you're right!

1069
01:12:13,867 --> 01:12:17,644
It is a good deal.

1070
01:12:17,667 --> 01:12:22,548
Phil, why don't you go on
back in the <i>woods</i>

1071
01:12:22,567 --> 01:12:25,912
and talk to the Lord.

1072
01:12:25,934 --> 01:12:30,314
Let him take controlling interest in
your life.

1073
01:12:30,334 --> 01:12:34,214
Begin to feel his power at work.

1074
01:12:58,501 --> 01:13:00,811
Listen to Phil, Lord,

1075
01:13:00,834 --> 01:13:04,111
just like you listened
to John and to me

1076
01:13:04,134 --> 01:13:06,774
<i>so</i> many times.

1077
01:13:25,067 --> 01:13:27,599
God, are you there?

1078
01:13:27,600 --> 01:13:29,705
Can you hear me?

1079
01:13:31,334 --> 01:13:34,577
I think I need you, Lord.

1080
01:13:36,267 --> 01:13:39,578
I'm getting really tired
of doing this on my own.

1081
01:13:43,301 --> 01:13:46,399
I'm just tired of being
a control freak, God

1082
01:13:46,400 --> 01:13:49,904
and telling everybody
what to do all the time.

1083
01:13:52,434 --> 01:13:55,745
Just forgive me, God.

1084
01:13:55,767 --> 01:14:01,080
Forgive me for being <i>so</i>
self-centered and...

1085
01:14:01,100 --> 01:14:04,843
Just such a jerk.

1086
01:14:06,367 --> 01:14:09,177
Forgive me for that,
will ya?

1087
01:14:09,200 --> 01:14:11,840
Could you do that?

1088
01:14:13,367 --> 01:14:17,066
Just change me, Jesus.

1089
01:14:17,067 --> 01:14:19,877
Okay?

1090
01:14:21,301 --> 01:14:25,113
I give you controlling interest.

1091
01:14:25,134 --> 01:14:30,550
Just come and take control
of my life.

1092
01:14:30,567 --> 01:14:33,066
Will ya?

1093
01:14:33,067 --> 01:14:36,699
And give me peace.

1094
01:14:36,700 --> 01:14:42,514
I just give it to you.

1095
01:14:45,401 --> 01:14:48,007
Is that a deal?

1096
01:14:49,634 --> 01:14:52,638
Have I got a deal, Lord?

1097
01:14:54,267 --> 01:14:56,474
Deal!!

1098
01:14:57,734 --> 01:15:01,079
It's a good deal!

1099
01:16:21,401 --> 01:16:24,382
The test was pretty hard.

1100
01:16:24,401 --> 01:16:28,144
I hate chemistry and when
I'm done with this class,

1101
01:16:28,167 --> 01:16:30,613
I'm never getting near it again.

1102
01:16:30,634 --> 01:16:35,533
But there is this guy in the class
I-l kinda like him.

1103
01:16:35,534 --> 01:16:40,142
He's cute, but I don't even think he
knows I exist.

1104
01:16:40,167 --> 01:16:44,479
But. . .college is <i>so</i> different.

1105
01:16:44,500 --> 01:16:49,500
But lately, I was thinking about
even getting into teaching

1106
01:16:50,667 --> 01:16:56,208
'cuz I-I remembered how much
it really meant to you

1107
01:16:56,234 --> 01:16:59,704
and it's. . .it's kind...

1108
01:17:16,767 --> 01:17:19,771
Teri...

1109
01:17:22,434 --> 01:17:28,874
I. . .Love. . .You.

1110
01:17:31,900 --> 01:17:33,799
Mommy...

1111
01:17:33,800 --> 01:17:37,199
You know who I am.

1112
01:17:37,200 --> 01:17:40,306
I love you too.

1113
01:17:42,367 --> 01:17:45,007
Mom...

1114
01:17:45,034 --> 01:17:47,537
I'm going to go get
Kyle and Dad,

1115
01:17:47,567 --> 01:17:49,638
I'll be right back, Mom.

1116
01:17:53,200 --> 01:17:56,374
John!

1117
01:17:58,400 --> 01:17:59,666
Ellen!

1118
01:17:59,667 --> 01:18:01,000
Mom!! Ellen!!

1119
01:18:01,001 --> 01:18:02,866
Mom!!

1120
01:18:02,867 --> 01:18:06,033
Ellen, honey...

1121
01:18:06,034 --> 01:18:08,071
Ellen?

1122
01:18:09,334 --> 01:18:11,678
She looked
right at me.

1123
01:18:11,701 --> 01:18:13,908
She said my name.

1124
01:18:16,801 --> 01:18:18,781
It's all right.

1125
01:18:20,834 --> 01:18:24,441
Maybe it was God's gift to you.

1126
01:18:32,967 --> 01:18:36,633
Looks like you finally found
the studs to that shirt.

1127
01:18:36,634 --> 01:18:39,133
Got a little class
working for you there

1128
01:18:39,134 --> 01:18:40,511
just like your
little brother.

1129
01:18:40,534 --> 01:18:41,911
Thanks.

1130
01:18:43,234 --> 01:18:45,578
You know, John, we ah,

1131
01:18:45,601 --> 01:18:48,333
we want you back
at the firm.

1132
01:18:48,334 --> 01:18:51,400
I want you back
as controlling partner.

1133
01:18:51,401 --> 01:18:54,133
Now you don't have
to answer to me right now,

1134
01:18:54,134 --> 01:18:56,799
I. . .l know you got a lot
on your mind and stuff.

1135
01:18:56,800 --> 01:18:59,940
There is one other thing
I want to clear up.

1136
01:18:59,967 --> 01:19:02,948
I ah...

1137
01:19:04,967 --> 01:19:09,313
I need you to forgive me--
for the way I acted,

1138
01:19:09,334 --> 01:19:12,213
for ah...

1139
01:19:12,234 --> 01:19:15,215
Putting the company
ahead of Ellen.

1140
01:19:16,934 --> 01:19:20,006
Will you forgive me
for that?

1141
01:20:00,167 --> 01:20:04,809
I, Kyle, take you, Cindy,
to be my beloved wife.

1142
01:20:04,834 --> 01:20:07,799
To have and to hold you,

1143
01:20:07,800 --> 01:20:10,371
to honor and treasure you,

1144
01:20:10,400 --> 01:20:13,779
to be by your side
in sorrow and in joy,

1145
01:20:13,800 --> 01:20:17,600
in sickness and in health,

1146
01:20:17,601 --> 01:20:20,946
to love and cherish you always.

1147
01:20:20,967 --> 01:20:25,882
I promise you this
with my heart,

1148
01:20:25,901 --> 01:20:28,999
with my soul...

1149
01:20:29,000 --> 01:20:32,733
As long as we both shall live.

1150
01:20:32,734 --> 01:20:36,113
This is my promise to you.

1151
01:20:56,267 --> 01:20:59,840
Yes, it is beautiful, isn't it?

